🔹 Step 1: Start the program

🔹 Step 2: Display menu options
1.Show Traffic Rules
2.Check Speed
3.Check Helmet
4.Check Seatbelt
5.Exit

🔹 Step 3: Read user choice

🔹 Step 4: Check user choice using switch-case
➤ Case 1: Show Rules
Call showRules()
Display all traffic rules
➤ Case 2: Check Speed
Input speed
If speed ≤ 60 → Display “Safe”
Else if speed ≤ 80 → Display “Fine ₹500”
Else → Display “Fine ₹1000”
➤ Case 3: Check Helmet
Input helmet (1/0)
If 1 → No fine
Else → Fine ₹500
➤ Case 4: Check Seatbelt
Input seatbelt (1/0)
If 1 → No fine
Else → Fine ₹500
➤ Case 5: Exit
Terminate program
➤ Default
Display “Invalid choice”

🔹 Step 5: Repeat steps 2–4 until user selects Exit

🔹 Step 6: Stop the program
